1
00:00:51,020 --> 00:00:55,320
[7 years ago]

2
00:01:12,180 --> 00:01:13,830
Seo Jong Hui?

3
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:22,050
What's the matter? Is something wrong-

4
00:01:23,370 --> 00:01:24,930
Oppa.

5
00:01:27,990 --> 00:01:30,610
Please...

6
00:01:30,610 --> 00:01:32,530
help me.

7
00:02:03,480 --> 00:02:05,750
This is the last train to Seoul.

8
00:02:13,430 --> 00:02:15,590
Thank you, Oppa.

9
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:21,750
Take it with you.

10
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:23,450
The night air is cold.

11
00:02:23,450 --> 00:02:25,490
You've got nothing on you.

12
00:02:31,810 --> 00:02:34,390
Aren't you going to ask...

13
00:02:38,990 --> 00:02:40,790
what happened?

14
00:02:41,610 --> 00:02:44,665
Most things have cause and effect,

15
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:48,115
but it's better not to know the cause sometimes.

16
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:04,450
I'm sorry. This is all I have.

17
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:08,140
Thank you, Oppa.

18
00:03:10,990 --> 00:03:12,910
I'll never forget...

19
00:03:15,650 --> 00:03:17,680
your help today.

20
00:03:58,680 --> 00:04:00,630
[Please Do Not Disturb]

21
00:04:02,730 --> 00:04:04,410
[Room 948]

22
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:26,730
Hey. Did anyone here clean Room 948 today?

23
00:04:30,810 --> 00:04:33,050
Well...

24
00:04:33,050 --> 00:04:35,860
there was a "Do Not Disturb"
sign hanging on the door.

25
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:39,380
Gosh, that's so unsettling.

26
00:04:41,690 --> 00:04:45,700
All of you, keep a close watch for now.

27
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:51,000
It's been four days since check-in,
and they haven't come out at all.

28
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:54,620
Without room service, they're
probably skipping meals as well.

29
00:04:54,620 --> 00:04:56,190
You're all aware, right?

30
00:04:56,190 --> 00:05:01,100
For a hotel, the ones who come alone
and shut themselves in are the scariest.

31
00:05:02,660 --> 00:05:07,070
If someone ends up dead,
our necks are on the line, too.

32
00:05:11,170 --> 00:05:14,070
What's going on? So scary...

33
00:05:17,230 --> 00:05:19,550
Gosh, it's so scary.

34
00:05:37,390 --> 00:05:40,750
[Please Do Not Disturb]

35
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:59,300
[I'm leaving the meal at your door.
Please have a bite to eat.]

36
00:07:05,980 --> 00:07:07,660
[Thank you for everything. Thanks for caring.]

37
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:15,030
Excuse me.

38
00:07:15,030 --> 00:07:17,070
Excuse me. Is anyone inside?

39
00:07:17,070 --> 00:07:20,710
Excuse me! Open the door! Excuse me!

40
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:27,160
Team Leader, I need the spare
key to Room 948. Hurry!

41
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:30,760
Excuse me!

42
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:36,490
- Ma'am!
- Stay away.

43
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:38,730
Please don't come near me.

44
00:07:38,730 --> 00:07:41,330
Please calm down.

45
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:42,950
Please stay back. Please...

46
00:07:42,950 --> 00:07:44,340
All right.

47
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:46,540
I won't come closer.

48
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:49,940
Do whatever you can to stop that guest.

49
00:07:49,940 --> 00:07:52,440
I'll call 119*. Got it?
(Emergency services in Korea)

50
00:07:55,930 --> 00:07:57,700
It's me.

51
00:07:58,470 --> 00:08:00,540
The one who left the note.

52
00:08:06,970 --> 00:08:08,670
When I was little,

53
00:08:08,670 --> 00:08:12,650
both of my parents died in an accident.

54
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,820
Back then, it really felt like the world had ended.

55
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:20,850
Life felt like a punishment,

56
00:08:22,050 --> 00:08:25,380
and there were more miserable
days than happy ones.

57
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:31,370
But I'm still here. Holding on.

58
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:37,660
Hoping this misery will pass.

59
00:08:38,810 --> 00:08:40,550
So...

60
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:44,030
please don't give up.

61
00:08:46,490 --> 00:08:49,430
In the end, it will pass. All of it.

62
00:08:53,410 --> 00:08:55,430
It'll pass, sure.

63
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:59,630
Gradually get duller.

64
00:09:00,960 --> 00:09:03,910
My late daughter will fade from my memory, too.

65
00:09:05,830 --> 00:09:07,900
I don't want that.

66
00:09:08,845 --> 00:09:12,120
I want to hurry up and go meet her.

67
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:14,300
I miss her so much.

68
00:09:14,300 --> 00:09:17,330
- So much.
- But if you do that,

69
00:09:17,330 --> 00:09:19,940
would your daughter be happy to see you?

70
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,950
I wouldn't if it were me.

71
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:28,230
I'd just be heartbroken.

72
00:09:29,740 --> 00:09:33,530
Knowing my mom took her own life because of me.

73
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:47,490
Your daughter would want you to have a good life.

74
00:09:47,490 --> 00:09:49,990
Be happy enough for both of you.

75
00:09:57,590 --> 00:10:00,240
To see flowers in spring,

76
00:10:02,010 --> 00:10:04,460
endure the summers, and...

77
00:10:05,730 --> 00:10:10,830
to think of her for a moment
when the sky turns crisp in autumn.

78
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:19,060
Do you really think so? Truly?

79
00:11:43,330 --> 00:11:47,120
All the new arrivals this season are power suits.

80
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:49,410
My taste runs more classic.

81
00:11:49,410 --> 00:11:51,950
I guess it's the trend.

82
00:11:51,950 --> 00:11:54,640
But this style isn't really me, either.

83
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:56,320
As the economy grows,

84
00:11:56,320 --> 00:12:00,240
flaunting wealth and power is
bound to become fashionable.

85
00:12:04,620 --> 00:12:07,380
How about trying switching up your style?

86
00:12:07,380 --> 00:12:12,250
How you present your appearance
can shape a person's mind.

87
00:12:14,820 --> 00:12:16,750
You have a more classic line, right?

88
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:18,150
Yes.

89
00:12:24,870 --> 00:12:26,950
Oh, my goodness.

90
00:12:26,950 --> 00:12:28,900
You look gorgeous.

91
00:12:28,900 --> 00:12:31,970
This style is new to me,
so it feels a bit awkward.

92
00:12:31,970 --> 00:12:34,780
No. It suits you way better than I expected.

93
00:12:34,780 --> 00:12:36,700
Look.

94
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:38,480
It's like it was made for her, right?

95
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:41,820
Yes, Chairwoman. It looks great on her.

96
00:12:41,820 --> 00:12:45,090
By the way, I didn't realize
you had a second daughter.

97
00:12:45,090 --> 00:12:47,150
She looks just like you.

98
00:12:47,150 --> 00:12:48,950
She's really beautiful.

99
00:12:48,950 --> 00:12:50,120
Right?

100
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:53,450
We're practically twins, aren't we?

101
00:13:00,010 --> 00:13:02,890
I came to help you shop.

102
00:13:02,890 --> 00:13:05,530
But you bought me way too many things.

103
00:13:05,530 --> 00:13:08,750
The things you got me last time
still have the tags on.

104
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:12,030
Wear them. Why keep them on display?

105
00:13:12,030 --> 00:13:14,040
I'll buy you more when the
season and trends change.

106
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,630
Wear them while you're pretty.

107
00:13:15,630 --> 00:13:17,590
I already have plenty.

108
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:20,900
No. Honestly, it's too much.

109
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:25,980
You're just right, Jong Hui.

110
00:13:25,980 --> 00:13:28,510
Not over the top, and not lacking.

111
00:13:29,400 --> 00:13:32,930
Thanks to you, I've become so stable lately.

112
00:13:32,930 --> 00:13:38,370
Sometimes, I even think
my Seung Yeon sent you to me.

113
00:13:38,370 --> 00:13:40,390
I'm happy, too.

114
00:13:41,430 --> 00:13:44,450
Thanks to you, I get to shop at a department store

115
00:13:44,450 --> 00:13:47,190
and have tea in a place this lovely.

116
00:13:47,190 --> 00:13:51,210
If it weren't for you, when would
I ever enjoy such luxury?

117
00:13:51,210 --> 00:13:52,970
Which brings me to ask,

118
00:13:52,970 --> 00:13:56,400
why don't you just stay with me like this?

119
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,540
Sorry?

120
00:13:57,540 --> 00:14:00,930
I'm proposing to you right now.

121
00:14:00,930 --> 00:14:05,040
Would you be my daughter? My adopted daughter?

122
00:14:15,820 --> 00:14:18,220
I just had the wallpaper redone.

123
00:14:18,220 --> 00:14:20,690
I don't know if you like it.

124
00:14:22,530 --> 00:14:24,250
It's so pretty.

125
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:25,730
Really?

126
00:14:26,730 --> 00:14:30,350
It's gorgeous, but it's my first time
in such a spacious room.

127
00:14:30,350 --> 00:14:32,710
When I worked as a bus attendant,

128
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:36,960
our dorm had a dozen girls in a room
not even half this size.

129
00:14:45,020 --> 00:14:46,570
Look…

130
00:14:49,020 --> 00:14:53,060
From now on, I'd rather you didn't
talk about the past.

131
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:56,670
I'd prefer you didn't stay in contact
with people from the past, either.

132
00:14:59,210 --> 00:15:04,040
You're starting a new life with me now.

133
00:15:22,700 --> 00:15:29,270
[Episode 8: Among So Many Stars]

134
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,300
- Jong Hui-
- Mom.

135
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:38,060
I don't have much time today.

136
00:15:38,060 --> 00:15:39,900
My class schedule is really tight.

137
00:15:39,900 --> 00:15:43,070
I know. But you can spare an hour, right?

138
00:15:43,070 --> 00:15:47,000
Oh, my. Your daughter is so beautiful.

139
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,250
How should I say this?

140
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:54,100
From an artist's standpoint,
I'm itching to style her from head to toe.

141
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,440
She's such a perfect model.

142
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:57,710
Oh, really?

143
00:15:57,710 --> 00:15:59,690
It may be lip service, but it's nice to hear.

144
00:15:59,690 --> 00:16:03,530
Gosh, Chairwoman, lip service? No way.

145
00:16:03,530 --> 00:16:07,870
I may not look it, but I can't
say things I don't mean.

146
00:16:07,870 --> 00:16:13,020
That's why people sometimes say
I'm not cut out to run a business.

147
00:16:13,020 --> 00:16:14,150
Shall we head up?

148
00:16:14,150 --> 00:16:17,020
You'd like to sit side by side, right?

149
00:16:17,020 --> 00:16:19,480
- Yes.
- Right this way.

150
00:16:22,880 --> 00:16:24,620
Be careful.

151
00:16:37,650 --> 00:16:41,650
Hello. I'm Jo Yeong Won, the manager at Jullee.

152
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:55,430
Hello. I'm a staff designer, Ko Yeong Rye.

153
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:04,970
Yes, hello.

154
00:17:04,970 --> 00:17:07,350
Thanks in advance.

155
00:17:07,350 --> 00:17:08,800
Excuse me.

156
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:10,020
Yes?

157
00:17:10,020 --> 00:17:12,920
My daughter doesn't like looking
overly done, so keep it natural.

158
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:15,200
Done, but not too done.

159
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:17,170
She really doesn't like anything flashy.

160
00:17:17,170 --> 00:17:19,400
Understood, Chairwoman.

161
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:23,980
We'll keep it simple.
No cut. Just a light blowout.

162
00:17:28,870 --> 00:17:30,120
Oh, my gosh!

163
00:17:30,120 --> 00:17:32,770
Oh, my goodness!

164
00:17:32,770 --> 00:17:34,630
That must've scared you!

165
00:17:35,810 --> 00:17:37,000
You should've been more careful!

166
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:40,440
She has a fear of sharp objects.
She's very sensitive!

167
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:44,110
I'm so sorry.

168
00:17:44,110 --> 00:17:47,020
I rarely make a mistake like this.

169
00:17:48,020 --> 00:17:49,140
Are you okay?

170
00:17:49,140 --> 00:17:51,060
Y-Yes. I'm fine.

171
00:17:51,970 --> 00:17:53,740
We're so sorry.

172
00:17:53,740 --> 00:17:56,260
I'm so sorry, Chairwoman.
She's usually not like that.

173
00:17:56,260 --> 00:17:57,870
Apologize.

174
00:17:57,870 --> 00:17:59,690
I'm sorry.

175
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,190
I'm so sorry. That was startling, wasn't it?

176
00:18:05,190 --> 00:18:08,020
I'm so sorry.

177
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:09,570
I'm sorry, but...

178
00:18:09,570 --> 00:18:11,400
Yes, go ahead.

179
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:14,300
I'm sorry, but...

180
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:20,010
I'd like to have her do the blowout today.
Is that possible?

181
00:18:20,010 --> 00:18:21,410
Sorry?

182
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:24,990
Oh, yes! Of course.

183
00:18:24,990 --> 00:18:28,900
Ms. Ko's hands are very skillful.

184
00:18:28,900 --> 00:18:30,530
Ms. Ko?

185
00:18:30,530 --> 00:18:32,000
Yes.

186
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:35,770
Switch.

187
00:18:36,730 --> 00:18:41,590
Then, I'll take care of you today.

188
00:18:51,510 --> 00:18:54,480
If you do this for a few minutes and take it out,

189
00:18:54,480 --> 00:18:58,510
you get nice curls, just like
you used a curling iron.

190
00:18:58,510 --> 00:19:00,500
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

191
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:02,140
Where'd you learn this?

192
00:19:02,140 --> 00:19:03,480
My mom's know-how.

193
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:07,320
I'm even thinking of getting
a cosmetology license, just in case.

194
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:08,790
Let me see.

195
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:43,990
We're very sorry for startling you earlier.

196
00:19:43,990 --> 00:19:49,410
I'll train them properly to prevent
such mishaps in the future.

197
00:19:49,410 --> 00:19:52,390
Do you like how it turned out today?

198
00:19:52,390 --> 00:19:54,510
Yes, I like it.

199
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:59,260
That's so good to hear.

200
00:19:59,260 --> 00:20:00,830
Please, take care on your way.

201
00:20:00,830 --> 00:20:03,080
Sure. Good work, everyone.

202
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:11,670
Please take care.

203
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:28,290
Goodbye.

204
00:20:28,290 --> 00:20:31,130
- Goodbye!
- Thank you for coming to Jullee.

205
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,770
Good work, Ms. Ko.

206
00:20:39,210 --> 00:20:41,080
Get rid of her!

207
00:20:43,820 --> 00:20:45,790
Ma'am...

208
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:07,210
[Yeong Sik's Baekban]

209
00:21:07,210 --> 00:21:09,990
[Love and Jeotgal for You]

210
00:21:09,990 --> 00:21:11,410
[Love and Jeotgal for You]

211
00:21:12,970 --> 00:21:15,570
What did I say is most crucial in sales?

212
00:21:15,570 --> 00:21:18,420
Display. The first law of the show window.

213
00:21:18,420 --> 00:21:21,000
In three seconds of looking at a display,

214
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:23,780
the brand image is burned into a customer's mind.

215
00:21:23,780 --> 00:21:25,980
Look. Don't you want to buy it already?

216
00:21:25,980 --> 00:21:28,110
Can't you line these up?

217
00:21:28,110 --> 00:21:29,390
Gosh, how uplifting!

218
00:21:29,390 --> 00:21:31,520
Gosh, how discouraging.

219
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:33,230
Hey, why be discouraged?

220
00:21:33,230 --> 00:21:36,640
Do you know h-how important this is?

221
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:40,710
The "Love and Jeotgal" label needs to stand out.

222
00:21:40,710 --> 00:21:42,920
Will this work? Maybe in different sizes-

223
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:44,660
Uncle!

224
00:21:44,660 --> 00:21:46,400
Gosh, my little Su Jin!

225
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:48,470
That's enough. You'll make her dizzy.

226
00:21:48,470 --> 00:21:50,360
She just ate a tray full of dumplings.

227
00:21:50,360 --> 00:21:51,720
What if she throws up?

228
00:21:51,720 --> 00:21:53,400
Su Jin, get down.

229
00:21:53,400 --> 00:21:56,250
You're heavy now. His arm will give out.

230
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:59,780
Are you worried about me or the kid?

231
00:21:59,780 --> 00:22:02,690
Pick a lane, will you? You're confusing people.

232
00:22:02,690 --> 00:22:05,040
What's confusing? Huh?

233
00:22:05,040 --> 00:22:07,960
I don't have time to spar with you.
Just put her down.

234
00:22:07,960 --> 00:22:11,810
Good grief. That mouth of yours, Ahjumma.

235
00:22:14,780 --> 00:22:16,170
There.

236
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:21,600
Hey, it must be your day off.

237
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:23,940
You're not wearing your blood-red lipstick today.

238
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:26,790
None of your business, really.

239
00:22:26,790 --> 00:22:28,870
Hey!

240
00:22:29,870 --> 00:22:32,830
I was going to ask.

241
00:22:34,040 --> 00:22:35,480
Did Su Jin get her vaccinations?

242
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:37,050
What vaccinations?

243
00:22:37,050 --> 00:22:39,680
See? You forgot again, didn't you?

244
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:42,480
I asked if she got her second
chickenpox shot last month

245
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:46,020
and you said to butt out saying
you'd do it this month.

246
00:22:46,020 --> 00:22:47,110
You still haven't?

247
00:22:47,110 --> 00:22:50,640
I can do it now. I just forgot.

248
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:53,330
There's stuff you shouldn't forget!

249
00:22:53,330 --> 00:22:55,270
Honestly, what kind of mom...

250
00:22:55,270 --> 00:22:59,230
Who's Su Jin supposed to rely on
in this rough world?

251
00:22:59,230 --> 00:23:02,910
Wait? Why is she so warm? Does she have a fever?

252
00:23:02,910 --> 00:23:05,150
Oh, stop it. What fever?

253
00:23:05,150 --> 00:23:07,130
Hold on.

254
00:23:07,130 --> 00:23:10,160
W-What are you doing?

255
00:23:13,730 --> 00:23:16,280
She's running a fever.

256
00:23:16,280 --> 00:23:18,320
Seriously!

257
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:20,400
A low-grade fever is still a fever for kids.

258
00:23:20,400 --> 00:23:24,110
Temperature is everything for jeotgal.
I know my temperatures.

259
00:23:24,110 --> 00:23:28,180
Su Jin, let's go to the hospital, okay? Got it?

260
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:33,070
Hey, wait. I'm coming, too.

261
00:23:45,770 --> 00:23:49,300
The lady asked me to bring you.

262
00:24:15,970 --> 00:24:17,800
Ko Yeong Rye!

263
00:24:24,520 --> 00:24:26,060
It's really you, right?

264
00:24:26,060 --> 00:24:28,560
I missed you so, so much.

265
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:30,220
Jong Hui?

266
00:24:31,120 --> 00:24:32,570
This isn't a dream, is it?

267
00:24:32,570 --> 00:24:34,300
It really is you, right?

268
00:24:34,300 --> 00:24:36,370
Yeah, it's me.

269
00:24:36,370 --> 00:24:38,360
The eun-ddo*, Ko Yeong Rye.
(Low-key psycho)

270
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:42,080
Are you really Seo Jong Hui?
The Seo Jong Hui I know?

271
00:24:42,080 --> 00:24:43,800
Yeah, it's me.

272
00:24:43,800 --> 00:24:47,380
That crazy, hopeless Seo Jong Hui.

273
00:24:47,380 --> 00:24:49,450
Gosh!

274
00:24:54,650 --> 00:24:58,560
So, that's how you became her adopted daughter.

275
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:01,570
I guess fate really does exist.

276
00:25:01,570 --> 00:25:02,990
Exactly.

277
00:25:02,990 --> 00:25:06,650
I never imagined my life would turn out this way.

278
00:25:06,650 --> 00:25:08,520
You were hurt earlier, weren't you?

279
00:25:08,520 --> 00:25:11,080
Because I acted like I didn't know you.

280
00:25:11,080 --> 00:25:14,420
I was quite surprised,

281
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:17,670
but I figured you must've had a reason.

282
00:25:17,670 --> 00:25:22,310
My mom doesn't like talking about the past.

283
00:25:22,310 --> 00:25:24,320
Or meeting people from the past, either.

284
00:25:24,320 --> 00:25:27,850
Really? Then maybe I shouldn't be here?

285
00:25:27,850 --> 00:25:29,070
She's not coming home today.

286
00:25:29,070 --> 00:25:33,620
She's at some kind of regional
business-leaders' forum or something.

287
00:25:39,430 --> 00:25:41,710
It honestly feels like a dream.

288
00:25:41,710 --> 00:25:44,170
Sitting here with you like this.

289
00:25:45,350 --> 00:25:46,790
Me, too.

290
00:25:47,620 --> 00:25:49,670
How's that? Does it hurt or not?

291
00:25:49,670 --> 00:25:50,950
It hurts!

292
00:25:50,950 --> 00:25:53,670
It hurts like crazy!

293
00:25:53,670 --> 00:25:56,610
You caught me off guard, eun-ddo Ko Yeong Rye.

294
00:25:58,020 --> 00:26:03,070
And your vibe has really changed.

295
00:26:03,070 --> 00:26:04,760
- Really?
- Yeah.

296
00:26:06,340 --> 00:26:08,210
Not as much as you.

297
00:26:08,210 --> 00:26:12,300
I've only changed on the outside.

298
00:26:12,300 --> 00:26:15,910
You feel tougher somehow.

299
00:26:16,890 --> 00:26:19,280
I can't really explain it,

300
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:21,940
but you've gotten really cool.

301
00:26:21,940 --> 00:26:25,140
You even look professional at the salon.

302
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:26,820
That's work.

303
00:26:26,820 --> 00:26:29,190
You know how I get hooked on things.

304
00:26:29,190 --> 00:26:33,530
Right. You were always something else.

305
00:26:33,530 --> 00:26:37,190
Let me show you my room. Come on.

306
00:26:37,190 --> 00:26:38,660
Come on.

307
00:26:41,170 --> 00:26:43,160
It's super pink, isn't it?

308
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:46,050
It's more of my mom's style than mine.

309
00:26:46,050 --> 00:26:49,030
I'm standing in for the daughter
she lost, you know.

310
00:26:49,030 --> 00:26:52,290
I try to make everything the way she wants.

311
00:26:56,230 --> 00:26:57,970
Do you want one?

312
00:26:58,970 --> 00:27:02,390
I quit a while back. Mom can't stand it.

313
00:27:02,390 --> 00:27:06,870
I still use it sometimes to calm me down.

314
00:27:06,870 --> 00:27:08,430
Oh, right.

315
00:27:15,250 --> 00:27:16,700
Yeong Rye, do you want to try this on?

316
00:27:16,700 --> 00:27:18,070
I think it'll look amazing on you.

317
00:27:18,070 --> 00:27:20,270
No, why would I take your clothes?

318
00:27:20,270 --> 00:27:24,620
Since when did we ever draw the line
between yours and mine?

319
00:27:24,620 --> 00:27:27,580
It's a present from me. Wear it, okay?

320
00:27:27,580 --> 00:27:29,260
Okay then.

321
00:27:29,260 --> 00:27:31,830
Thanks, I'll wear it well.

322
00:27:50,860 --> 00:27:52,760
[Youngin University]

323
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:54,250
You're attending college?

324
00:27:54,250 --> 00:27:56,020
Yeah.

325
00:27:56,020 --> 00:27:59,710
Mom said she'd like me to get
a diploma even if it's late.

326
00:27:59,710 --> 00:28:01,710
Equestrian studies.

327
00:28:01,710 --> 00:28:03,250
What about you?

328
00:28:03,250 --> 00:28:06,100
Did you give up on college?

329
00:28:06,100 --> 00:28:08,710
Going to college was your dream.

330
00:28:08,710 --> 00:28:11,460
I didn't give up yet.

331
00:28:11,460 --> 00:28:14,180
I'm going to try for a night program this year.

332
00:28:14,180 --> 00:28:18,090
I still need to help out
with living expenses for now.

333
00:28:18,090 --> 00:28:21,140
That's tough. Working and studying.

334
00:28:21,140 --> 00:28:22,630
Sit.

335
00:28:24,980 --> 00:28:27,430
How's your mom? And Yeong Bae and Yeong Mi?

336
00:28:27,430 --> 00:28:29,580
Mom runs a small restaurant

337
00:28:29,580 --> 00:28:32,990
called Yeong Sik's Baekban in Yeongeun Market.

338
00:28:32,990 --> 00:28:34,840
Yeong Bae and Yeong Mi are in middle school.

339
00:28:34,840 --> 00:28:36,520
Already?

340
00:28:36,520 --> 00:28:38,760
I really miss them.

341
00:28:38,760 --> 00:28:40,000
What about Yeong Sik?

342
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,750
Oppa passed the national exams

343
00:28:41,750 --> 00:28:44,890
and he's currently at the Judicial
Research and Training Institute.

344
00:28:44,890 --> 00:28:46,510
Really?

345
00:28:46,510 --> 00:28:49,200
I knew he'd pull it off.

346
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:51,060
That's awesome.

347
00:28:53,450 --> 00:28:55,310
What about Jae Pil?

348
00:28:57,190 --> 00:28:59,710
Are you still in touch with him?

349
00:28:59,710 --> 00:29:03,300
Yeah, he's doing well.

350
00:29:03,300 --> 00:29:06,530
He got into med school, and he's
an intern at a university hospital.

351
00:29:06,530 --> 00:29:09,700
Jae Pil got into medical school?

352
00:29:09,700 --> 00:29:12,390
It wasn't smooth sailing.

353
00:29:12,390 --> 00:29:15,780
Their department store went bankrupt,

354
00:29:15,780 --> 00:29:18,350
and his father suddenly collapsed.

355
00:29:19,510 --> 00:29:22,330
All Jae Pil could do was study.

356
00:29:22,330 --> 00:29:24,340
Are you good with pain?

357
00:29:27,350 --> 00:29:30,830
For inpatients, the biggest risk is falling.

358
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:33,340
If you wander around without your parents

359
00:29:33,340 --> 00:29:36,740
and get hurt again,
you'll be in big trouble. Okay?

360
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:40,240
Does it hurt?

361
00:29:40,240 --> 00:29:41,590
Yes.

362
00:29:43,020 --> 00:29:46,260
If you're curious, want to meet
him together sometime?

363
00:29:46,260 --> 00:29:47,780
Hold your breath.

364
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:51,170
No.

365
00:29:51,170 --> 00:29:54,000
No matter how I think about it,
that's just not right.

366
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:57,480
I practically kicked him to the curb.

367
00:29:57,480 --> 00:30:00,410
Still, Jae Pil worries about you-

368
00:30:00,410 --> 00:30:03,100
Hey, it's pretty late. Just take our car.

369
00:30:03,100 --> 00:30:04,380
I'll tell the driver.

370
00:30:04,380 --> 00:30:06,290
It's okay. There are still buses running.

371
00:30:06,290 --> 00:30:07,870
I can just take the bus.

372
00:30:07,870 --> 00:30:10,730
Former bus attendant here. I'm comfy on buses.

373
00:30:10,730 --> 00:30:12,830
You don't get carsick anymore?

374
00:30:12,830 --> 00:30:14,350
From time to time.

375
00:30:14,350 --> 00:30:17,890
Only if I'm feeling off or when it rains.

376
00:30:17,890 --> 00:30:20,130
I'm still a country bumpkin.

377
00:30:22,660 --> 00:30:24,120
Here.

378
00:30:26,090 --> 00:30:30,680
I wrote in this journal whenever I thought of you.

379
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:33,650
I don't think I need it anymore.

380
00:30:33,650 --> 00:30:35,850
I want you to have it.

381
00:30:43,280 --> 00:30:49,760
I really, really missed you.

382
00:30:51,430 --> 00:30:55,560
I even went near your place behind my mom's back.

383
00:30:55,560 --> 00:30:58,990
I couldn't find the house
in the end due to redevelopment.

384
00:30:58,990 --> 00:31:00,540
Me, too.

385
00:31:01,630 --> 00:31:05,050
I really missed you, too.

386
00:31:06,250 --> 00:31:09,540
I just had no idea how to even start looking.

387
00:31:10,540 --> 00:31:13,030
You didn't even show up in my dreams.

388
00:31:14,100 --> 00:31:15,590
Really?

389
00:31:15,590 --> 00:31:16,700
Yeah.

390
00:31:18,640 --> 00:31:21,200
You're not getting away now.

391
00:31:21,200 --> 00:31:25,010
I've got you again, okay?

392
00:31:25,010 --> 00:31:28,210
Don't you try to run off on me.

393
00:31:28,210 --> 00:31:31,390
I'm not letting you go this time.

394
00:31:33,170 --> 00:31:34,820
Go in and sleep.

395
00:31:34,820 --> 00:31:38,000
- Don't get all worked up and toss and turn.
- Okay.

396
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,230
- I'll go now.
- Bye.

397
00:31:40,230 --> 00:31:42,330
Bye.

398
00:31:42,330 --> 00:31:44,200
Yeong Rye!

399
00:31:44,200 --> 00:31:47,510
I'll show up in your dream tonight!

400
00:31:47,510 --> 00:31:49,420
See you there!

401
00:31:50,380 --> 00:31:52,860
- I'm off.
- Bye.

402
00:31:53,860 --> 00:31:55,460
Bye!

403
00:32:38,220 --> 00:32:42,600
Yeong Rye, every day feels so long.

404
00:32:42,600 --> 00:32:46,660
I wake up, work, eat just to stay alive.

405
00:32:46,660 --> 00:32:49,590
I beg for sleep that won't come.

406
00:32:49,590 --> 00:32:52,240
And I'm afraid of tomorrow.

407
00:32:53,810 --> 00:32:58,270
Will radiant days like the ones I spent with you

408
00:32:58,270 --> 00:33:00,820
ever come to me again?

409
00:33:12,170 --> 00:33:15,630
Yeong Rye, a miracle happened to me.

410
00:33:15,630 --> 00:33:19,310
I became a rich family's daughter.

411
00:33:20,380 --> 00:33:23,940
If you'd been with me,
you'd have been so happy for me.

412
00:33:23,940 --> 00:33:27,360
I finally have a family who loves me.

413
00:33:31,660 --> 00:33:33,860
Today, I craved ramen so badly.

414
00:33:33,860 --> 00:33:37,080
So, I went out and ate it behind Mom's back.

415
00:33:37,080 --> 00:33:40,400
But it didn't taste like
it used to on the rooftop.

416
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:44,760
I don't really miss the ramen…

417
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:47,600
but I just miss you so much.

418
00:34:26,740 --> 00:34:28,550
I had a dream.

419
00:34:29,510 --> 00:34:32,740
That man was chasing me,
blood pouring out of him.

420
00:34:33,770 --> 00:34:37,240
Since I didn't see any news reports,
I guess he didn't die.

421
00:34:37,240 --> 00:34:39,620
But why didn't he report it?

422
00:34:41,430 --> 00:34:44,530
I'm still so scared, Yeong Rye.

423
00:35:37,470 --> 00:35:41,790
Sir. Sir, I'm sorry, but could you open the door?

424
00:35:41,790 --> 00:35:43,700
Thank you.

425
00:37:09,690 --> 00:37:11,140
Hey.

426
00:37:12,310 --> 00:37:13,970
What did you just say?

427
00:37:13,970 --> 00:37:15,660
Once I dug out one thing,

428
00:37:15,660 --> 00:37:19,430
the corruption kept coming out like a vine.

429
00:37:19,430 --> 00:37:23,600
You forced innocent attendants
to take the blame for embezzlement,

430
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:28,740
and meanwhile, the manager has been
fiddling with the books and embezzling?

431
00:37:28,740 --> 00:37:31,250
Over the course of more than ten years?

432
00:37:31,250 --> 00:37:36,400
As if that wasn't enough, you even used
that money to buy off the police.

433
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:38,950
If HQ finds out- no...

434
00:37:38,950 --> 00:37:40,650
HQ would be the least of your worries.

435
00:37:40,650 --> 00:37:42,410
Hey, Ko Yeong Rye.

436
00:37:42,410 --> 00:37:44,870
What are you trying to get at?

437
00:37:48,900 --> 00:37:54,300
Take that night's incident to your grave.

438
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:59,840
After all, Jong Hui's action was self-defense.

439
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:05,260
Even if you try to press charges,
I will testify to that to the end.

440
00:38:05,260 --> 00:38:09,910
In the end, you'll be the one
who steps on the landmine.

441
00:38:11,050 --> 00:38:13,490
So...

442
00:38:13,490 --> 00:38:17,110
just bury the whole thing.

443
00:39:04,820 --> 00:39:06,430
Tell me this.

444
00:39:07,430 --> 00:39:10,730
Why do bean sprouts have heads?

445
00:39:10,730 --> 00:39:13,640
How great would it be not to have to trim them?

446
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:17,910
We're trimming them because
we're making spicy braised monkfish.

447
00:39:17,910 --> 00:39:20,420
The heads actually have more nutrients.

448
00:39:20,420 --> 00:39:21,830
Really?

449
00:39:21,830 --> 00:39:24,140
Do the heads actually have more nutrients?

450
00:39:24,140 --> 00:39:26,830
Nothing goes to waste with bean sprouts.

451
00:39:26,830 --> 00:39:28,080
They're easy to grow,

452
00:39:28,080 --> 00:39:32,620
and both the head and the stem
are full of nutrients.

453
00:39:32,621 --> 00:39:52,831
Officail Website: dramacool.club

454
00:39:52,855 --> 00:40:13,065
Translate by =Qari= @Team Viki

455
00:39:34,090 --> 00:39:35,360
Like Yeong Rye?

456
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:37,820
- What? Our Yeong Rye?
- Yeah.

457
00:39:37,820 --> 00:39:39,790
Yeong Rye's like that, Unni.

458
00:39:39,790 --> 00:39:43,890
Smart, does her work well,

459
00:39:43,890 --> 00:39:46,130
and she's got a good personality, too.

460
00:39:46,130 --> 00:39:49,820
She's a dutiful daughter and treats
her siblings with great devotion.

461
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:55,280
Even that rigid Mr. Han Gi Bok
would drop everything for her.

462
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:59,050
There's nothing to fault. She's one in a million.

463
00:39:59,050 --> 00:40:01,200
Is that so?

464
00:40:01,200 --> 00:40:03,970
Which brings me to the point, Unni.

465
00:40:05,370 --> 00:40:08,570
I'll get to the point. What do you
think about our Jae Pil?

466
00:40:08,570 --> 00:40:10,990
That was out of the blue.

467
00:40:10,990 --> 00:40:12,380
Why bring Jae Pil up suddenly?

468
00:40:12,380 --> 00:40:17,030
Honestly, how can a man and
a woman be "just friends"?

469
00:40:17,030 --> 00:40:18,770
They've known each other for many years.

470
00:40:18,770 --> 00:40:22,470
When they're always together,
there's bound to be something.

471
00:40:22,470 --> 00:40:26,120
Everybody at the hospital already
thinks they're a couple.

472
00:40:26,120 --> 00:40:29,070
Well, I suppose you could read it that way.

473
00:40:29,070 --> 00:40:35,490
Hey, this could mess up Yeong Rye's
chances of getting married.

474
00:40:35,490 --> 00:40:37,220
It's not a laughing matter.

475
00:40:37,220 --> 00:40:41,620
We should get them paired up before it's too late.

476
00:40:41,620 --> 00:40:44,240
Well, now that we're talking,

477
00:40:44,240 --> 00:40:47,900
our Jae Pil doesn't lack anything, either.

478
00:40:47,900 --> 00:40:52,910
He's straight-laced, good-looking,
and has a solid job.

479
00:40:52,910 --> 00:40:55,930
It's a strike against him that
his family's business went belly-up.

480
00:40:55,930 --> 00:40:59,170
That really isn't a deal-breaker.

481
00:40:59,170 --> 00:41:02,790
But is this something we can decide ourselves?

482
00:41:02,790 --> 00:41:05,120
They've got to have feelings for each other.

483
00:41:05,120 --> 00:41:07,580
If it's meant to be, they'll end up
together, no matter what.

484
00:41:07,580 --> 00:41:09,940
If it's not, no amount
of pushing will change that.

485
00:41:09,940 --> 00:41:12,610
You can't make a monk shave his own head.

486
00:41:12,610 --> 00:41:15,400
Anyway, you're okay with it, right?

487
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:17,110
Okay or not.

488
00:41:17,110 --> 00:41:20,100
Didn't you say you had an
appointment? I think it's about time.

489
00:41:20,100 --> 00:41:22,930
Oh, my! How did it get so late?

490
00:41:22,930 --> 00:41:24,730
Oh, no, I'm late. I'm late!

491
00:41:24,730 --> 00:41:26,290
- Go.
- Okay, then.

492
00:41:26,290 --> 00:41:29,880
At any rate, you said okay! Okay it is.

493
00:41:35,620 --> 00:41:37,440
Really?

494
00:42:01,100 --> 00:42:05,400
Ho Suk, put this inside and boil a pot of water.

495
00:42:05,400 --> 00:42:06,960
All right.

496
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:08,350
Excuse me.

497
00:42:08,350 --> 00:42:10,770
- Welcome. Would you like something to eat?
- Welcome.

498
00:42:10,770 --> 00:42:12,490
No, ma'am.

499
00:42:12,490 --> 00:42:14,770
This is for you.

500
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:18,560
Goodbye.

501
00:42:18,560 --> 00:42:21,540
- Oh, my. What's all that?
- Wait, what...

502
00:42:22,500 --> 00:42:23,870
What's all that?

503
00:42:23,870 --> 00:42:26,570
- Did you order this?
- Is this really for us?

504
00:42:26,570 --> 00:42:28,540
- I don't know.
- Who sent it?

505
00:42:28,540 --> 00:42:30,940
- He just left this.
- What is all this?

506
00:42:30,940 --> 00:42:33,320
- Bananas are expensive.
- What is all this?

507
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:35,230
- Oh, my.
- Oh, my!

508
00:42:36,170 --> 00:42:38,480
Who sent this?

509
00:42:39,860 --> 00:42:43,240
Would you like something to eat?

510
00:42:44,820 --> 00:42:46,480
Ho Suk.

511
00:42:49,230 --> 00:42:50,460
Mother.

512
00:42:50,460 --> 00:42:53,060
- W-Who are you?
- Who are you?

513
00:42:54,330 --> 00:42:55,610
I'm Jong Hui.

514
00:42:55,610 --> 00:43:00,630
I used to be friends with Yeong Rye
at Cheongah Transportation.

515
00:43:00,630 --> 00:43:03,060
Jong Hui?

516
00:43:03,060 --> 00:43:05,530
The one who used to come to our house?

517
00:43:05,530 --> 00:43:09,110
Yes. That's me. Jong Hui.

518
00:43:09,110 --> 00:43:12,000
Oh, my goodness!

519
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:14,320
Aigoo!

520
00:43:15,500 --> 00:43:18,250
It really is you, isn't it?

521
00:43:18,250 --> 00:43:22,280
How have you been all this time?

522
00:43:22,280 --> 00:43:25,630
Alive or dead, you should've sent word.

523
00:43:25,630 --> 00:43:28,000
Yeong Rye was worried sick about you.

524
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:29,620
I'm sorry.

525
00:43:29,620 --> 00:43:31,180
I'm so sorry, Mother.

526
00:43:31,180 --> 00:43:33,620
You're alive, so we meet again.

527
00:43:33,620 --> 00:43:35,920
Since you're alive.

528
00:43:35,920 --> 00:43:37,240
I'm home.

529
00:43:37,240 --> 00:43:39,150
Me, too.

530
00:43:46,660 --> 00:43:50,070
Yeong Bae and Yeong Mi?

531
00:43:51,760 --> 00:43:53,720
Guys!

532
00:43:53,720 --> 00:43:55,800
They've grown up, haven't they?

533
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:01,600
What? Jong Hui?

534
00:44:02,600 --> 00:44:06,140
Daeyang Group's only daughter
is the same Seo Jong Hui we know?

535
00:44:07,300 --> 00:44:11,870
I'm so shocked that my stomach
twisted up just now.

536
00:44:11,870 --> 00:44:15,020
At first, I thought I was mistaken, too.

537
00:44:15,020 --> 00:44:19,270
But it really was Jong Hui.

538
00:44:19,270 --> 00:44:22,080
Even hearing it, I still can't believe it.

539
00:44:22,080 --> 00:44:24,660
Gosh, how could Jong Hui…

540
00:44:24,660 --> 00:44:26,350
Goodness.

541
00:44:26,350 --> 00:44:31,140
She said she saved her life and
became her adopted daughter.

542
00:44:31,140 --> 00:44:33,310
Isn't it so dramatic?

543
00:44:33,310 --> 00:44:35,920
So like Seo Jong Hui.

544
00:44:35,920 --> 00:44:40,170
I was so stunned yesterday and
couldn't believe it myself

545
00:44:40,170 --> 00:44:42,590
that I couldn't tell you.

546
00:44:58,120 --> 00:45:01,340
- Jong Hui!
- Hey. Ko Yeong Rye, you're here?

547
00:45:01,340 --> 00:45:04,700
Jong Hui, what are you doing here?

548
00:45:04,700 --> 00:45:07,970
What's going on?

549
00:45:07,970 --> 00:45:10,130
Oh, my goodness.

550
00:45:10,130 --> 00:45:13,280
Gosh, look who this is.

551
00:45:15,910 --> 00:45:18,790
It's really our Seo Jong Hui.

552
00:45:18,790 --> 00:45:21,490
Yeah, Unni. It's really me.

553
00:45:21,490 --> 00:45:23,470
You rotten little brat.

554
00:45:23,470 --> 00:45:26,070
Where the hell have you been all this time?

555
00:45:26,070 --> 00:45:29,090
I know. I'm sorry.

556
00:45:30,160 --> 00:45:32,080
Hey, you're here?

557
00:45:32,080 --> 00:45:33,400
Hey.

558
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:38,310
I told her to stay upstairs,
but she insisted on helping out.

559
00:45:38,310 --> 00:45:40,770
You don't know how quick Jong Hui's hands are.

560
00:45:40,770 --> 00:45:42,740
Customers swarmed in tonight.

561
00:45:42,740 --> 00:45:44,680
We would've had it tough without her.

562
00:45:44,680 --> 00:45:46,230
But Mom, why did you make her serve-

563
00:45:46,230 --> 00:45:49,450
I begged her to let me do this.

564
00:45:49,450 --> 00:45:53,700
I had to do something
to eat her dinner tonight. Right?

565
00:45:53,700 --> 00:45:56,780
You didn't eat yet, right? You can eat with me.

566
00:45:59,650 --> 00:46:00,990
What?

567
00:46:10,300 --> 00:46:11,740
Bye.

568
00:46:11,740 --> 00:46:14,370
And tell your driver-

569
00:46:14,370 --> 00:46:15,670
Don't worry.

570
00:46:15,670 --> 00:46:18,700
I already told him you all once helped me.

571
00:46:18,700 --> 00:46:20,550
He's tight-lipped.

572
00:46:20,550 --> 00:46:22,550
Thank goodness.

573
00:46:22,550 --> 00:46:25,070
I should go. Go inside first. I'll see you off.

574
00:46:25,070 --> 00:46:26,430
It's okay.

575
00:46:26,430 --> 00:46:27,820
Go on.

576
00:46:27,820 --> 00:46:31,580
All right. I'll go. Have a safe drive.

577
00:46:33,790 --> 00:46:35,270
Bye!

578
00:46:36,490 --> 00:46:38,100
Goodbye.

579
00:46:48,830 --> 00:46:50,610
Seo Jong Hui!

580
00:46:53,170 --> 00:46:55,300
Yeong Sik?

581
00:46:55,300 --> 00:46:57,270
It's really you.

582
00:47:11,270 --> 00:47:13,460
I called home, and Yeong Bae told me.

583
00:47:13,460 --> 00:47:16,570
I wouldn't have believed it if
I hadn't seen you myself.

584
00:47:16,570 --> 00:47:18,440
I'm glad.

585
00:47:20,080 --> 00:47:23,290
But you haven't changed much, Oppa.

586
00:47:23,290 --> 00:47:26,640
Maybe I'm wrong. You seem
to have gotten more handsome.

587
00:47:27,640 --> 00:47:29,510
You've changed a lot.

588
00:47:29,510 --> 00:47:32,430
I don't think I'd recognize you on the street.

589
00:47:32,430 --> 00:47:34,100
Right?

590
00:47:34,100 --> 00:47:35,880
I think so, too.

591
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:38,380
Sometimes, I look in the mirror and get startled,

592
00:47:38,380 --> 00:47:40,910
wondering if it's really me.

593
00:47:45,340 --> 00:47:48,910
I wanted to meet you at least once.

594
00:47:49,960 --> 00:47:53,050
You saved my life, after all.

595
00:47:53,050 --> 00:47:55,370
Come on. That's not true.

596
00:47:55,370 --> 00:47:56,920
No, really.

597
00:47:57,810 --> 00:48:01,000
If it hadn't been for you that day,

598
00:48:01,000 --> 00:48:04,430
I never would've dared come to Seoul.

599
00:48:04,430 --> 00:48:06,740
I have a long way to go.

600
00:48:06,740 --> 00:48:08,650
When my mom had that accident,

601
00:48:08,650 --> 00:48:12,780
don't you remember we got back
on our feet, thanks to you?

602
00:48:12,780 --> 00:48:16,590
When I make real money, I'll pay you back first.

603
00:48:16,590 --> 00:48:18,330
It's fine.

604
00:48:18,330 --> 00:48:21,390
Pay me back with meals, then.
Maybe a hundred times?

605
00:48:25,800 --> 00:48:29,300
These past few days have felt like a dream.

606
00:48:29,300 --> 00:48:31,470
Yeong Rye, Mother,

607
00:48:31,470 --> 00:48:35,210
Yeong Bae, Yeong Mi, Jeong Bun, and Ho Suk.

608
00:48:35,210 --> 00:48:37,230
And even you, Oppa.

609
00:48:38,040 --> 00:48:41,110
I got to see everyone I wanted to see.

610
00:48:50,050 --> 00:48:52,210
What?

611
00:48:52,210 --> 00:48:55,470
Are you sure you got to see
everyone you wanted to see?

612
00:48:55,470 --> 00:48:57,340
Isn't there more?

613
00:49:01,370 --> 00:49:07,040
You've always had a knack
for seeing right through people.

614
00:49:07,040 --> 00:49:10,050
Do you know what I was always
envious of about Yeong Rye?

615
00:49:10,050 --> 00:49:12,600
That she has a brother like you.

616
00:49:17,650 --> 00:49:20,180
I've taken up too much of your time.

617
00:49:20,180 --> 00:49:22,520
I'll take up more of your time in the future.

618
00:49:22,520 --> 00:49:24,510
Shall we go now?

619
00:49:37,680 --> 00:49:40,150
I got a call from home earlier.

620
00:49:40,150 --> 00:49:42,400
Chairwoman is home.

621
00:49:42,400 --> 00:49:44,900
- Mom?
- Yes.

622
00:49:57,410 --> 00:49:59,570
Thank you for everything.

623
00:50:09,000 --> 00:50:10,210
Mom.

624
00:50:10,210 --> 00:50:11,560
You're home?

625
00:50:11,560 --> 00:50:13,580
How are you home already?

626
00:50:13,580 --> 00:50:15,470
I thought you were coming tomorrow.

627
00:50:15,470 --> 00:50:17,690
That was the plan, but I was tired.

628
00:50:17,690 --> 00:50:20,490
So, I just rode with President Shin in his car.

629
00:50:20,490 --> 00:50:22,060
You should've called.

630
00:50:22,060 --> 00:50:24,950
The driver would've gone immediately.

631
00:50:24,950 --> 00:50:28,070
But what's with the car outside?

632
00:50:28,070 --> 00:50:30,050
Did you see it?

633
00:50:30,050 --> 00:50:31,760
Look at the situation today.

634
00:50:31,760 --> 00:50:34,050
It would've been better if you had your own car.

635
00:50:34,050 --> 00:50:36,670
Don't refuse and use it. It's your gift.

636
00:50:36,670 --> 00:50:39,160
Mom, I'm really okay.

637
00:50:39,160 --> 00:50:41,660
Just take it. The world is too dangerous.

638
00:50:41,660 --> 00:50:43,310
They say strike while the iron is hot.

639
00:50:43,310 --> 00:50:46,400
I just finished interviewing
a driver for your car.

640
00:50:46,400 --> 00:50:49,270
Say hello. She'll be using the car.

641
00:50:51,880 --> 00:50:54,260
Hello. My name is Kim Jeong Sik.

642
00:50:54,260 --> 00:50:56,710
You can just call me Mr. Kim...

643
00:51:00,900 --> 00:51:04,200
- By any chance-
- How do you do?

644
00:51:05,300 --> 00:51:07,330
Ah, yes.

645
00:51:07,330 --> 00:51:11,180
For a moment, I thought you were
someone I used to know

646
00:51:11,180 --> 00:51:13,340
because you look so much like her.

647
00:51:13,340 --> 00:51:14,920
There's no way that's possible.

648
00:51:14,920 --> 00:51:17,190
Thank you in advance.

649
00:51:17,190 --> 00:51:19,920
Oh, right. Remember tomorrow
at Operia Hotel, right?

650
00:51:19,920 --> 00:51:22,300
With the second son of Seongwoo Group.

651
00:51:22,300 --> 00:51:25,550
It's just for a cup of tea, so no pressure.

652
00:51:25,550 --> 00:51:28,410
If it goes well, even better.

653
00:51:45,000 --> 00:51:47,500
I've polished it all nice and shiny.

654
00:51:47,500 --> 00:51:50,800
So it won't detract from your beauty. Please-

655
00:52:29,220 --> 00:52:31,790
You are. Right?

656
00:52:31,790 --> 00:52:35,650
Your name was Seo something.

657
00:52:35,650 --> 00:52:37,120
Seo Jong Hui.

658
00:52:37,120 --> 00:52:39,480
That's it! Seo Jong Hui.

659
00:52:39,480 --> 00:52:43,630
Ms. Seo, how... Wow, life is so funny.

660
00:52:43,630 --> 00:52:45,340
Your life is like a movie.

661
00:52:45,340 --> 00:52:48,680
Yesterday, I was a bit unsure.

662
00:52:48,680 --> 00:52:52,030
But seeing you today, it's so clear.

663
00:52:52,030 --> 00:52:56,810
The shape of your eyes and that slender jawline.

664
00:52:56,810 --> 00:52:59,330
I was right.

665
00:52:59,330 --> 00:53:02,540
I've got a good eye, even for a man.

666
00:53:02,540 --> 00:53:04,510
I'm sure.

667
00:53:04,510 --> 00:53:06,630
To scout women to pick up.

668
00:53:06,630 --> 00:53:10,030
No need to be so blunt.

669
00:53:10,030 --> 00:53:11,860
How embarrassing.

670
00:53:12,970 --> 00:53:15,240
I've changed a lot.

671
00:53:15,240 --> 00:53:20,420
Forget the old, unbearably
frivolous Mr. Kim. Please.

672
00:53:23,930 --> 00:53:26,660
I'll forget. In return,

673
00:53:27,520 --> 00:53:29,780
please forget my past, too.

674
00:53:29,780 --> 00:53:31,260
Especially in front of my mom.

675
00:53:31,260 --> 00:53:34,520
Of course. I already caught on.

676
00:53:34,520 --> 00:53:37,690
Don't worry. When I make up my mind,

677
00:53:37,690 --> 00:53:41,710
I can be an incredibly tight-lipped person.

678
00:53:41,710 --> 00:53:44,220
We're going to Operia Hotel, right?

679
00:53:49,000 --> 00:53:51,630
Ahjumma, what brings you here?

680
00:53:51,630 --> 00:53:53,540
Gosh, you must be busy.

681
00:53:53,540 --> 00:53:57,390
I was going to head straight
to the hospital after work,

682
00:53:57,390 --> 00:54:01,450
but a regular customer who lives nearby called

683
00:54:01,450 --> 00:54:04,470
and begged me to come, saying

684
00:54:04,470 --> 00:54:09,660
there's no other day that works except today.

685
00:54:09,660 --> 00:54:13,930
Could you take this to Jae Pil?

686
00:54:13,930 --> 00:54:17,820
It's clothes, underwear, and socks.

687
00:54:17,820 --> 00:54:20,170
I'm sure he's completely out and probably urgent.

688
00:54:20,170 --> 00:54:21,320
Okay, I will.

689
00:54:21,320 --> 00:54:24,370
I'm not on the closing shift today,
so I can leave a bit early.

690
00:54:24,370 --> 00:54:29,000
Oh, really? That's even better.

691
00:54:29,000 --> 00:54:34,860
While you're there, ask Jae Pil to buy you
dinner at the hospital cafeteria.

692
00:54:34,860 --> 00:54:36,690
The food is all right there.

693
00:54:36,690 --> 00:54:38,470
They even serve Western food sometimes.

694
00:54:38,470 --> 00:54:41,410
No, it's fine. Jae Pil is busy.

695
00:54:41,410 --> 00:54:43,600
What do you mean busy...

696
00:54:43,600 --> 00:54:48,810
Yes, he's busy. He is busy, but still ask him.

697
00:54:48,810 --> 00:54:52,200
He'll buy you dinner. Of course, he will.

698
00:54:52,200 --> 00:54:55,870
It's not just anybody. It's you, Yeong Rye.

699
00:54:57,550 --> 00:54:58,860
I will, then.

700
00:54:58,860 --> 00:55:01,600
I'll happily let him treat me. Don't worry.

701
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:05,660
Great. That's good. Good.

702
00:55:05,660 --> 00:55:07,080
Get back inside.

703
00:55:07,080 --> 00:55:09,390
All right. Thanks!

704
00:55:12,320 --> 00:55:13,760
Success.

705
00:55:25,920 --> 00:55:28,630
[Ms. Seo Jong Hui]

706
00:55:51,930 --> 00:55:53,750
Mr. Jo Hyeon Woo?

707
00:55:53,750 --> 00:55:57,320
Yes. You're Seo Jong Hui, right?

708
00:55:58,410 --> 00:56:00,620
I've heard a lot about you.

709
00:56:05,740 --> 00:56:07,570
Please have a seat.

710
00:56:32,970 --> 00:56:34,470
How radiant.

711
00:56:34,470 --> 00:56:36,230
That color...

712
00:56:38,530 --> 00:56:40,710
They must be foreigners.

713
00:56:56,370 --> 00:56:58,980
I'll get going first.

714
00:56:58,980 --> 00:57:02,250
How about we watch a movie next time?

715
00:57:02,250 --> 00:57:06,220
No. I'll be busy that day.

716
00:57:07,160 --> 00:57:08,610
Bye now.

717
00:57:29,970 --> 00:57:32,540
I didn't even say what day.

718
00:57:47,930 --> 00:57:50,000
I guess you didn't like him.

719
00:57:51,520 --> 00:57:56,620
The guy did seem a bit boring
even at first glance.

720
00:57:56,620 --> 00:58:00,820
You know, like he was raised in a bubble?

721
00:58:00,820 --> 00:58:04,530
Like he grew up without much hardship, but-

722
00:58:04,530 --> 00:58:06,950
Let's go quietly.

723
00:58:06,950 --> 00:58:08,420
Sure.

724
00:58:18,370 --> 00:58:22,620
[Yeonseo University Hospital]

725
00:58:25,220 --> 00:58:28,450
Are you sure you got to see
everyone you wanted to see?

726
00:58:28,450 --> 00:58:30,350
Isn't there more?

727
00:58:37,300 --> 00:58:39,520
Mr. Kim, please turn back.

728
00:58:39,520 --> 00:58:41,890
I need to stop by somewhere.

729
00:58:41,890 --> 00:58:43,270
Okay.

730
00:59:25,120 --> 00:59:26,980
Han Jae Pil!

731
00:59:26,980 --> 00:59:28,900
Yeong Rye.

732
00:59:30,860 --> 00:59:33,150
Go on ahead.

733
00:59:33,150 --> 00:59:34,580
What are you doing here?

734
00:59:34,580 --> 00:59:36,210
Here.

735
00:59:36,210 --> 00:59:38,650
- What's this?
- Man Ok ahjumma's errand.

736
00:59:38,650 --> 00:59:41,340
She says it's your clothes, underwear, and socks.

737
00:59:41,340 --> 00:59:42,960
She said she'll be late

738
00:59:42,960 --> 00:59:46,440
and asked me to bring it to you since it's urgent.

739
00:59:46,440 --> 00:59:47,860
Why would she...

740
00:59:47,860 --> 00:59:51,290
I have a few left, so it's not that urgent.

741
00:59:51,290 --> 00:59:52,550
Really?

742
00:59:52,550 --> 00:59:56,230
Then, why did she ask me? Maybe she was mistaken.

743
00:59:57,080 --> 00:59:59,370
You didn't look inside, did you?

744
00:59:59,370 --> 01:00:00,640
What?

745
01:00:00,640 --> 01:00:02,530
What I'm saying is...

746
01:00:04,050 --> 01:00:06,030
my underwear-

747
01:00:06,030 --> 01:00:09,110
Hey! You think I'm a pervert?

748
01:00:09,110 --> 01:00:13,130
Why would I look at that? You're ridiculous.

749
01:00:13,130 --> 01:00:17,760
If you didn't look, fine.
But why are you blushing so much?

750
01:00:18,820 --> 01:00:21,230
Huh? You saw it!

751
01:00:21,230 --> 01:00:24,130
Why would you look at my underwear?

752
01:00:24,130 --> 01:00:26,810
You want to die? Cut it out.

753
01:00:26,810 --> 01:00:29,200
All right. It hurts.

754
01:00:29,200 --> 01:00:32,800
Seriously. Quit the nonsense and buy me dinner.

755
01:00:32,800 --> 01:00:35,990
Ahjumma said to make sure you buy me dinner.

756
01:00:37,020 --> 01:00:38,720
Hold on. Your eyelash.

757
01:00:39,940 --> 01:00:43,670
You're supposed to cut hair, not your eyelashes.

758
01:00:43,670 --> 01:00:46,000
You're so clumsy.

759
01:00:47,250 --> 01:00:49,140
So, why did you look?

760
01:00:50,640 --> 01:00:52,470
I'll buy you dinner.

761
01:01:00,950 --> 01:01:03,280
Should I park the car or...

762
01:01:03,280 --> 01:01:05,030
Let's just go.

763
01:01:07,010 --> 01:01:09,010
My business is done here.

764
01:01:16,650 --> 01:01:19,110
Beans are loaded with plant protein.

765
01:01:19,110 --> 01:01:21,440
Good for bone density, prevents breast
cancer, and helps blood vessels.

766
01:01:21,440 --> 01:01:26,180
The world's best Cinderella crop,
and you won't eat them.

767
01:01:26,180 --> 01:01:30,630
Mom cooked bean rice so much
when I was little, and I'm sick of it.

768
01:01:30,630 --> 01:01:34,580
What about you? You can't handle
spicy food even as a grown-up.

769
01:01:34,580 --> 01:01:37,670
Such a kid, Han Jae Pil.

770
01:01:39,510 --> 01:01:42,940
Hey, I can handle spicy.

771
01:01:42,940 --> 01:01:45,730
I just don't like it.

772
01:01:47,470 --> 01:01:50,550
- You want to see me eat it?
- Hey, forget it.

773
01:01:50,550 --> 01:01:52,890
Don't fill your stomach with water.

774
01:01:52,890 --> 01:01:55,490
Here. Have some anchovies instead.

775
01:01:55,490 --> 01:01:57,560
Here you go.

776
01:01:58,840 --> 01:02:02,510
All right. Since I'm obedient to you.

777
01:02:11,790 --> 01:02:14,940
No matter how I think about it,
that's just not right.

778
01:02:14,940 --> 01:02:18,080
I practically kicked him to the curb.

779
01:02:20,320 --> 01:02:23,030
Hey, Jae Pil.

780
01:02:23,030 --> 01:02:24,960
Yeah?

781
01:02:24,960 --> 01:02:27,070
To tell you the truth,

782
01:02:28,070 --> 01:02:29,690
recently-

783
01:02:29,690 --> 01:02:32,810
Hey, Jae Pil! It's an emergency! Emergency...

784
01:02:33,990 --> 01:02:36,720
Chang Eui is freaking out again.

785
01:02:36,720 --> 01:02:37,910
He's gathering everyone.

786
01:02:37,910 --> 01:02:40,620
- Geez!
- Hurry.

787
01:02:40,620 --> 01:02:42,230
I'm really sorry. I should go.

788
01:02:42,230 --> 01:02:43,410
It's fine. Go ahead.

789
01:02:43,410 --> 01:02:46,360
Finish everything before you go. Okay?

790
01:02:46,360 --> 01:02:48,090
- Finish, okay?
- Yeah. Go!

791
01:02:48,090 --> 01:02:50,040
I'll buy you something good again. Sorry.

792
01:02:50,040 --> 01:02:51,740
I'm sorry!

793
01:03:29,870 --> 01:03:31,350
Thank you.

794
01:03:31,350 --> 01:03:34,350
I'll see you tomorrow. Good night.

795
01:04:47,590 --> 01:04:50,390
Wow, looking good around here.

796
01:04:50,390 --> 01:04:53,880
They say send horses to Jeju and people to Seoul.

797
01:04:53,880 --> 01:04:57,740
As expected of Seoul. Especially Gangnam.

798
01:05:01,510 --> 01:05:03,890
Isn't that Choi Jeong Bun?

799
01:05:08,430 --> 01:05:09,790
Bun!

800
01:05:09,790 --> 01:05:12,070
It really is you, Choi Jeong Bun.

801
01:05:12,070 --> 01:05:15,750
I wasn't sure if it was you.

802
01:05:15,750 --> 01:05:18,480
But it is. Gosh.

803
01:05:18,480 --> 01:05:19,900
Whoa!

804
01:05:19,900 --> 01:05:22,810
I was just passing by and

805
01:05:22,810 --> 01:05:25,500
saw a woman, who looks like you, walking down.

806
01:05:25,500 --> 01:05:28,830
Wow. How have you been?

807
01:05:28,830 --> 01:05:30,760
You've gotten prettier.

808
01:05:32,410 --> 01:05:36,430
We're not on good enough terms
to greet each other so happily.

809
01:05:36,430 --> 01:05:39,080
Huh? Hey, come on.

810
01:05:39,080 --> 01:05:40,710
You can't just leave like this.

811
01:05:40,710 --> 01:05:43,440
We have a past.

812
01:05:44,320 --> 01:05:46,950
How about we grab a cup of tea?

813
01:05:52,650 --> 01:05:55,930
If I have time to sit and chat with you over tea,

814
01:05:55,930 --> 01:05:59,570
I'd rather go home, wash my feet,
and get some sleep.

815
01:05:59,570 --> 01:06:02,690
Don't you think so? I'm not interested.

816
01:06:08,180 --> 01:06:12,290
She's so cold. The Siberian cold front
has nothing on her.

817
01:06:13,930 --> 01:06:16,540
She's even more attractive now.

818
01:06:18,340 --> 01:06:19,950
All right.

819
01:06:52,230 --> 01:06:54,470
I'm home.

820
01:07:18,000 --> 01:07:19,760
What is it?

821
01:07:19,760 --> 01:07:22,230
Who are you, ahjussi?

822
01:07:22,230 --> 01:07:23,680
Well, who are you?

823
01:07:23,680 --> 01:07:25,430
I'm Su Jin. Choi Su Jin.

824
01:07:25,430 --> 01:07:26,650
I see. Su Jin.

825
01:07:26,650 --> 01:07:29,110
You shouldn't wander around the market alone.

826
01:07:29,110 --> 01:07:30,420
Where are your mom and dad?

827
01:07:30,420 --> 01:07:32,630
My mom went to work over there.

828
01:07:32,630 --> 01:07:34,840
And my dad isn't here.

829
01:07:38,400 --> 01:07:40,260
Your dad isn't here?

830
01:07:40,260 --> 01:07:42,560
Why? Did he go somewhere?

831
01:07:42,560 --> 01:07:44,220
No, he's just not here.

832
01:07:44,220 --> 01:07:47,420
My dad was never here from the beginning.

833
01:07:47,420 --> 01:07:48,600
Oh, gosh!

834
01:07:48,600 --> 01:07:51,670
- Su Jin!
- Mom!

835
01:07:55,940 --> 01:07:57,500
I said I'm done with you.

836
01:07:57,500 --> 01:08:01,100
Why did you follow me all the way
here and bother my kid?

837
01:08:01,100 --> 01:08:04,000
I didn't bother her. She just asked me who I was.

838
01:08:04,000 --> 01:08:05,610
Forget it!

839
01:08:06,450 --> 01:08:09,960
Go. Just get out of here!

840
01:08:10,870 --> 01:08:12,440
What's wrong with you?

841
01:08:12,440 --> 01:08:14,620
I'm here to eat. Why are you getting mad?

842
01:08:14,620 --> 01:08:18,320
I'm not selling food to you. Just go.

843
01:08:18,320 --> 01:08:20,740
Can't you hear me? Huh?

844
01:08:20,740 --> 01:08:23,980
You make me shudder when I see you.

845
01:08:23,980 --> 01:08:26,970
Just go, will you?

846
01:08:26,970 --> 01:08:29,900
All right. I'm going. I'll go.

847
01:08:29,900 --> 01:08:32,070
Such an attitude.

848
01:08:36,810 --> 01:08:39,530
I'm sorry for yelling.

849
01:08:47,010 --> 01:08:48,910
[Jullee Beauty Salon]

850
01:08:48,910 --> 01:08:51,190
Yeong Rye!

851
01:08:51,190 --> 01:08:52,850
There's a flower basket at the door.

852
01:08:52,850 --> 01:08:55,130
Looks like it's addressed to you.

853
01:08:56,500 --> 01:08:59,710
[To: Ko Yeong Rye]
Who would send me this...

854
01:08:59,710 --> 01:09:01,150
Who is it from?

855
01:09:01,150 --> 01:09:03,380
Hey. Could it be from Jae Pil?

856
01:09:03,380 --> 01:09:06,930
Who else would send something like this to you?

857
01:09:06,930 --> 01:09:08,950
It's him. It's Han Jae Pil.

858
01:09:08,950 --> 01:09:13,440
How many blossoms are there? So many!

859
01:09:13,440 --> 01:09:16,930
Jae Pil wouldn't send something like this.

860
01:09:16,930 --> 01:09:19,790
You're right. I sent them.

861
01:09:22,190 --> 01:09:24,280
Not Jae Pil.

862
01:09:24,280 --> 01:09:26,200
Oppa!

863
01:09:33,110 --> 01:09:35,730
Why are there so many customers
asking for her lately?

864
01:09:35,730 --> 01:09:37,500
She'll become a manager in no time.

865
01:09:37,500 --> 01:09:39,470
That's what I'm saying.

866
01:09:39,470 --> 01:09:42,930
Is there some secret sales trick or something?

867
01:09:42,930 --> 01:09:44,790
Let's go.

868
01:09:51,300 --> 01:09:54,750
You have to tell me the style
you want before I cut.

869
01:09:54,750 --> 01:09:56,950
I won't complain even if it
looks like a rat chewed on it.

870
01:09:56,950 --> 01:10:00,080
So, do whatever style you want, Ms. Ko Yeong Rye.

871
01:10:00,080 --> 01:10:03,130
I'll gladly be your personal model.

872
01:10:03,130 --> 01:10:04,920
Try something bold and groundbreaking.

873
01:10:04,920 --> 01:10:08,240
What will you do if I just shave it all off?

874
01:10:08,240 --> 01:10:10,560
It won't matter since I'm handsome.

875
01:10:10,560 --> 01:10:13,690
I don't rely on my hair for good looks.

876
01:10:15,080 --> 01:10:18,610
I can't argue with that.

877
01:10:18,610 --> 01:10:23,740
Honestly, your head shape is really nice.

878
01:10:23,740 --> 01:10:25,490
It is.

879
01:10:27,770 --> 01:10:30,880
By the way, Yeong Rye, you've changed a lot.

880
01:10:30,880 --> 01:10:34,160
I have? How so?

881
01:10:34,160 --> 01:10:37,470
Remember when we talked about the
right to pursue happiness?

882
01:10:39,330 --> 01:10:44,390
I feel like you're finally enjoying that.

883
01:10:44,390 --> 01:10:48,580
You laugh more and speak your mind more clearly.

884
01:10:49,480 --> 01:10:54,020
I'm a little sad, though. You no longer
need me as your Daddy-Long-Legs.

885
01:10:54,020 --> 01:10:55,760
Not yet.

886
01:10:55,760 --> 01:10:57,880
I'll still give out the occasional SOS,

887
01:10:57,880 --> 01:11:00,600
so keep being my Daddy-Long-Legs.

888
01:11:02,680 --> 01:11:04,570
Oh, no!

889
01:11:04,570 --> 01:11:05,980
I cut too much.

890
01:11:05,980 --> 01:11:10,200
Hey, did you give me a bald patch? Hey...

891
01:11:10,200 --> 01:11:12,280
I'm just kidding.

892
01:11:12,280 --> 01:11:15,200
You said you wouldn't complain. What was that?

893
01:11:15,200 --> 01:11:17,670
I was just playing along, too.

894
01:11:18,910 --> 01:11:23,350
So, what time do you finish today,
Ms. Ko Yeong Rye?

895
01:11:24,180 --> 01:11:27,520
I'm not on the closing shift,
so in a couple more hours.

896
01:11:27,520 --> 01:11:30,760
Really? Should I wait and buy you dinner?

897
01:11:30,760 --> 01:11:32,830
Something expensive and fancy?

898
01:11:32,830 --> 01:11:35,960
I'd love that, but I have
a prior engagement today.

899
01:11:35,960 --> 01:11:37,830
Oh, yeah?

900
01:11:37,830 --> 01:11:39,700
What prior engagement?

901
01:12:16,040 --> 01:12:17,930
You want to die?

902
01:12:17,930 --> 01:12:19,460
I said I didn't see it.

903
01:12:19,460 --> 01:12:21,040
It hurts.

904
01:12:21,040 --> 01:12:22,980
Hold on. Your eyelash.

905
01:12:58,170 --> 01:12:59,520
This way.

906
01:13:03,700 --> 01:13:06,530
We transported her from a stable
after she lost consciousness from a fall.

907
01:13:06,530 --> 01:13:08,510
Her vitals are relatively stable,

908
01:13:08,510 --> 01:13:11,590
but there may have been an impact to the head.

909
01:13:11,590 --> 01:13:13,290
I got that. Thanks for your work.

910
01:13:13,290 --> 01:13:14,900
Thank you, Doctor.

911
01:13:14,900 --> 01:13:17,500
- Get an IV line started.
- Yes, Doctor.

912
01:13:38,460 --> 01:13:39,670
You shouldn't get up.

913
01:13:39,670 --> 01:13:42,350
Ma'am, it's all right! This is the hospital.
Please calm down.

914
01:13:42,350 --> 01:13:45,120
- Ma'am!
- Ma'am, please calm down.

915
01:14:24,920 --> 01:14:27,510
Didn't you hear the nurse? You can't leave yet.

916
01:14:27,510 --> 01:14:30,670
I'm fine. I'm not injured.

917
01:14:36,750 --> 01:14:38,180
I'm the doctor.

918
01:14:38,180 --> 01:14:40,460
Get examined before you go.

919
01:14:40,460 --> 01:14:43,160
Then and now, you haven't changed.

920
01:14:44,290 --> 01:14:47,120
You still have a knack for shocking people.

921
01:15:00,710 --> 01:15:02,470
Thanks so much, Oppa.

922
01:15:02,470 --> 01:15:04,750
Thanks to you, I could-

923
01:16:05,760 --> 01:16:07,850
Who do you mean by "The calm before the storm"?

924
01:16:07,850 --> 01:16:10,410
Yeong Rye. Jae Pil. Jong Hui.

925
01:16:10,410 --> 01:16:12,330
Who knows? And maybe also...

926
01:16:12,330 --> 01:16:13,710
I'm her boyfriend. Now what?

927
01:16:13,710 --> 01:16:16,470
You seem awfully close to Yeong Rye.

928
01:16:16,470 --> 01:16:18,300
She's a friend I can't live without now.

929
01:16:18,300 --> 01:16:20,350
Just a close friend?

930
01:16:20,350 --> 01:16:22,460
Out of people who brushed past my life,

931
01:16:22,460 --> 01:16:24,440
I used to think those who left are mere ties

932
01:16:24,440 --> 01:16:28,100
and the ones who stayed are destiny.

933
01:16:28,100 --> 01:16:30,630
As for the one who returns,

934
01:16:30,630 --> 01:16:34,180
is she a mere connection or destiny?

935
01:16:34,180 --> 01:16:35,900
Or...
